{"title_page": "Flatliners (2017 film)", "text_new": "{{short description|2017 film by Niels Arden Oplev}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name = Flatliners\n| image = Flatliners (2017).jpg\n| caption = Theatrical release poster\n| director = [[Niels Arden Oplev]]\n| producer = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Laurence Mark]]<ref name=\"producers\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/flatliners-trailer-remake-ellen-page-diego-luna-nina-dobrev-1202464050/|title=Ellen Page, Diego Luna, Nina Dobrev Experiment With Death in \u2018Flatliners\u2019 Trailer|last=McNary|first=Dave|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=June 13, 2017|accessdate=June 13, 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Michael Douglas]]<ref name=\"producers\"/>\n* [[Peter Safran]]<ref name=\"producers\"/>\n}}\n| screenplay = [[Ben Ripley]]\n| story = Peter Filardi\n| based on = {{based on|''[[Flatliners]]''|Peter Filardi}}\n| starring = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Ellen Page]]\n* [[Diego Luna]]\n* [[Nina Dobrev]]\n* [[James Norton (actor)|James Norton]]\n* [[Kiersey Clemons]]\n}}\n| music = [[Nathan Barr]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Nathan Barr to Score \u2018Flatliners|url=http://filmmusicreporter.com/2017/08/08/nathan-barr-to-score-flatliners/|website=Film Music Reporter|accessdate=September 9, 2017|date=August 8, 2017}}</ref>\n| cinematography = [[Eric Kress]]\n| editing = Tom Elkins\n| studio = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Columbia Pictures]]<ref name=\"insight\">{{cite web|url=http://www.varietyinsight.com/print_featurefilm_releases.php|title=Film releases|work=[[Variety Insight]]|accessdate=December 27, 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Cross Creek Pictures]]<ref name=\"insight\"/>\n* [[Further Films]]<ref name=\"insight\"/>\n* Laurence Mark Productions<ref name=\"insight\"/>\n* [[The Safran Company]]<ref name=\"insight\"/>\n}}\n| distributor = [[Sony Pictures Releasing]]\n| released = {{Film date|2017|9|29|United States}}\n| runtime = 110 minutes<ref name=\"15cert\">{{cite web|url=http://www.bbfc.co.uk/releases/flatliners-2017|title=FLATLINERS (15)|work=[[British Board of Film Classification]]|accessdate=September 20, 2017}}</ref>\n| country = United States\n| language = English\n| budget = $19 million<ref name=BOM/>\n| gross = $45.2 million<ref name=BOM>{{cite web|url=https://boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=flatliners2017.htm|title=Flatliners (2017)|work=[[Box Office Mojo]]|accessdate=January 30, 2018}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''Flatliners''''' is a 2017 American [[Science fiction film|science fiction]] [[psychological horror film]] directed by [[Niels Arden Oplev]] and written by [[Ben Ripley]]. The film is both a [[stand-alone sequel]] to and [[remake]] of the [[Flatliners|1990 film of the same name]], and stars [[Ellen Page]], [[Diego Luna]], [[Nina Dobrev]], [[James Norton (actor)|James Norton]], and [[Kiersey Clemons]]. It follows five medical students who attempt to conduct experiments that produce [[near-death experience]]s.\n\n[[Sony Pictures]] released the film in the United States on September 29, 2017. It was negatively reviewed by critics, who generally remarked that it repeated the problems of the original in failing to do justice to its interesting premise, but it was a moderate box office success, grossing $45 million worldwide on a $19 million budget.\n\n==Plot==\n<!-- 400 to 700 words only in this section. -->\nA medical student, Courtney, is obsessed with the idea of the afterlife. She invites fellow students Jamie and Sophia to join her in an experiment, in an unused hospital room: using defibrillation to stop her heart for sixty seconds while recording her brain. She assures them they would not be held responsible for any accidents. Sophia is against this, but Jamie does it anyway. After sixty seconds, they are unable to revive her. Fellow student Ray helps them resuscitate her. Marlo, a rival of Ray, arrives and learns of the experiment.\n\nCourtney begins to recall memories of past events such as her grandmother's recipe for bread. Courtney experiences increased intelligence and euphoria, being suddenly able to play the piano after 12 years and answer questions in class perfectly. Envious, Jamie flatlines, but has a disturbing [[near-death experience]] as he meets his ex-girlfriend. Marlo and Sophia follow suit and flatline, for an increasing number of minutes. During Sophia\u2019s turn they are nearly caught and flee the hospital and arrive at a party. Courtney and Jamie start seeing visions of past mistakes, but do not tell the others.\n\nThose who flatlined experience visions: Courtney is haunted by her sister Tessa, who died in a car crash she caused because she was using her phone. Jamie is haunted by the baby of his ex-girlfriend who he got pregnant and begged to get an abortion. Marlo is haunted by a man named Cyrus who died when she accidentally mixed up his medication, and Sophia is haunted by a girl named Irina whose life she ruined out of jealousy by hacking her phone and sending out her nudes. This allowed Sophia to become [[valedictorian]].\n\nCourtney, traumatised by her visions, records a message apologising for the consequences and admitting that her interest in flatlining was due to the death of her sister, not for scientific discovery. She falls to her death from the fire escape of her apartment building after her sister's ghost pushes her off. The others are devastated when they learn of Courtney\u2019s death, and realize they may be implicated if anyone discovers their experiments. After attempting to remove all notes and evidence from Courtney\u2019s apartment, Marlo is sent to the morgue to find Courtney\u2019s phone. She is once again haunted by visions. On his boat, Jamie again hears the cries of a baby and a woman weeping. He falls out of his boat and swims to the dock where a figure stabs him in his hand.\n\nThe group watches Courtney's recording and find out that she had encountered similar hauntings. They come clean to the mistakes they made and come to the conclusion that the hauntings they're experiencing are hallucinations because of guilt from their sins, not paranormal beings. The only one who didn't flatline, Ray, initially disbelieves what's happening.\n\nThe group takes action to stop the hallucinations by fixing their past mistakes. Sophia visits Irina to apologize, which Irina accepts. Jamie visits his ex-girlfriend and discovers she didn't get an abortion, but kept the baby; he apologizes and promises to provide for his son. Ray and Marlo get into a fight when Ray finds out Marlo covered up the real reason Cyrus died and she refuses to come clean. Marlo hallucinates being suffocated while driving and crashes her car. Tired of being haunted by her hallucinations, Marlo flatlines on her own in the hope of asking forgiveness of Cyrus. Ray, Sophia and Jamie rush to stop her. They resuscitate Marlo after she sees an apparition of Courtney, who tells Marlo that she needs to forgive herself. Marlo, Ray, Sophia and Jamie reminisce about Courtney and celebrate their friendships in the little restaurant they hang out at, where there is a performance of the piano piece that Courtney played. Jamie proposes a toast, honoring Courtney.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Ellen Page]] as Courtney Holmes<ref name=\"dobrev instagram\">{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BI_EoPXgSai/|title=Instagram post by Nina Dobrev \u2022 Aug 11, 2016 at 10:40pm UTC|website=Instagram}}</ref>\n* [[Diego Luna]] as Ray<ref name=\"dobrev instagram\"/>\n* [[Nina Dobrev]] as Marlo<ref name=\"dobrev instagram\"/>\n* [[James Norton (actor)|James Norton]] as Jamie<ref name=\"dobrev instagram\"/>\n* [[Kiersey Clemons]] as Sophia<ref name=\"dobrev instagram\"/>\n* [[Kiefer Sutherland]] as Dr. Barry Wolfson / Nelson Wright{{efn|A [[deleted scene]] identifies Wolfson as being an older version of Dr. Nelson Wright from the [[Flatliners|original film]], having changed his name.<ref name=\"sutherland reprise\">{{cite web|last1=Lee|first1=Ann|title=Kiefer Sutherland reveals who he's playing in the Flatliners reboot|url=http://metro.co.uk/2016/07/27/kiefer-sutherland-reveals-who-hes-playing-in-the-flatliners-reboot-6032883/|website=Metro|accessdate=13 October 2017|date=27 July 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"same character confirmed\">{{cite web|last1=Oplev|first1=Niels Arden|title=There\u2019s A Flatliners Deleted Scene That Connects The New Movie To The Original|url=https://www.cinemablend.com/news/1708220/theres-a-flatliners-deleted-scene-that-connects-the-new-movie-to-the-original|website=[[Cinema Blend]]|accessdate=28 September 2017|date=28 September 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n* [[Beau Mirchoff]] as Brad<ref>{{cite web|last1=Gallupo|first1=Mia|title='Awkward' Actor Beau Mirchoff Joining Sony's 'Flatliners' Reboot (Exclusive)|url=https://hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/awkward-actor-beau-mirchoff-joining-914820|website=The Hollywood Reporter|accessdate=6 October 2017|language=en|date=27 July 2016}}</ref>\n* Madison Brydges as Tessa Holmes\n* Miguel Anthony as Cyrus Gudgeon\n* [[Jenny Raven]] as Irina Wong\n* [[Charlotte McKinney]] as Girl on Bicycle\n* [[Janet Porter]] ''(uncredited)'' as ER Doctor\n* Jeremiah Sird as Dr. Velez\n\n==Production==\nIn October 2015, [[Ellen Page]] was cast in the film.<ref>{{cite news|last=Kroll|first=Justin |title=Ellen Page in Talks to Star in \u2018Flatliners\u2019 Remake (EXCLUSIVE)|url=https://variety.com/2015/film/news/ellen-page-flatliners-remake-julia-roberts-thriller-1201355718/ |accessdate=July 13, 2016|work=Variety|date=October 5, 2015}}</ref> In February 2016, [[Diego Luna]] was added,<ref>{{cite news|last=Geier|first=Thom|title='Rogue One' Star Diego Luna in Talks to Join Ellen Page in 'Flatliners'|url=http://www.thewrap.com/rogue-one-star-diego-luna-in-talks-to-join-ellen-page-in-sonys-flatliners-exclusive/|accessdate=July 13, 2016|work=TheWrap|date=February 29, 2016}}</ref> with [[Nina Dobrev]] joining in April.<ref>{{cite news|last=Patten|first=Dominic|title=Nina Dobrev In Talks To Join Sony\u2019s \u2018Flatliners\u2019 Reboot|url=https://deadline.com/2016/04/nina-dobrev-in-talks-star-sony-flatliners-reboot-1201741049/|accessdate=July 13, 2016|website=Deadline Hollywood |date=April 20, 2016}}</ref> In May 2016, [[Kiersey Clemons]] and [[James Norton (actor)|James Norton]] signed on for the film.<ref>{{cite news|last=Kroll|first=Justin |title=\u2018Dope\u2019s\u2019 Kiersey Clemons to Star Opposite Ellen Page in \u2018Flatliners\u2019 (EXCLUSIVE) |url=https://variety.com/2016/film/news/flatliners-remake-ellen-page-kiersey-clemons-1201765444/|accessdate=July 13, 2016|work=Variety|date=May 3, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Galuppo|first=Mia|title=James Norton Joins Ellen Page in 'Flatliners' Remake (Exclusive)|url=https://hollywoodreporter.com/news/james-norton-joins-ellen-page-892030|accessdate=July 13, 2016|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=May 9, 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2016, it was announced that [[Kiefer Sutherland]], who starred in the original, would return in the new film.<ref>{{cite news|last=Busch|first=Anita|title=Kiefer Sutherland Crossing Over To \u2018Flatliners\u2019 Redo|url=https://deadline.com/2016/07/kiefer-sutherland-joins-flatliners-reboot-movie-1201783469/|accessdate=July 13, 2016|website=Deadline Hollywood|date=July 7, 2016}}</ref> Sutherland later disclosed that he was reprising his role from the original film, adding that the new film is actually a sequel rather than a remake.<ref name=\"sutherland reprise\"/> Despite the announcement, Sutherland played a character with a different name than in the original, with no reference to the specific events of the previous film.{{Citation needed|date=October 2017}} In July 2016, [[Charlotte McKinney]] also joined the cast.<ref>{{cite web|last=Busch|first=Anita|title=Supermodel Charlotte McKinney Supercharges \u2018Flatliners\u2019|url=https://deadline.com/2016/07/charlotte-mckinney-supermodel-flatliners-reboot-1201785951/|website=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=6 October 2017|date=13 July 2016}}</ref>\n\n[[Principal photography]] began in early July 2016 in [[Toronto]],<ref>{{cite news|last=Eigenmann|first=Conan Geisler|title=\u2018The Vampire Diaries\u2019 star Ian Somerhalder's ex Nina Dobrev filming \u2018Flatliners\u2019 remake; Kiefer Sutherland returns as doctor |url=http://en.yibada.com/articles/140110/20160711/vampire-diaries-star-nina-dobrev-filming-flatliners-remake-kiefer-sutherland.htm|accessdate=July 13, 2016|work=YIBADA|date=July 11, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Lesnick|first=Silas|title=Flatliners Reboot Set for 2017 Release - ComingSoon.net|url=https://comingsoon.net/movies/news/701839-flatliners-reboot-2017|accessdate=July 13, 2016|work=ComingSoon.net|date=July 12, 2016}}</ref> [[Ontario]] primarily at [[Cinespace Film Studios]]' [[Kipling Avenue]] facility, and concluded on September 7.{{Citation needed|date=October 2017}} The film went into post-production on October 4.<ref>{{cite news|last=Hime|first=Nelly|title=The Flatliners Remake \u2013 Everything You Need to Know|url=http://nagamedigital.com/2016/08/29/flatliners-remake/|accessdate=October 9, 2016|work=Nagame Digital|date=August 29, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161009210452/http://nagamedigital.com/2016/08/29/flatliners-remake/|archive-date=October 9, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n[[Nathan Barr]] composed the film score. The soundtrack was released by [[Sony Classical]].\n\n==Release==\n\n===Box office===\n''Flatliners'' grossed $16.9 million in the United States and Canada, and $28.1 million in other territories, for a worldwide total of $45 million, against a production budget of $19 million.<ref name=\"BOM\"/>\n\nIn North America, the film was released alongside ''[[American Made (film)|American Made]]'' and ''[['Til Death Do Us Part (film)|'Til Death Do Us Part]]'', as well as the wide expansion of ''[[Battle of the Sexes (2017 film)|Battle of the Sexes]]'', and was projected to gross $8\u201312 million from 2,552 theaters in its opening weekend.<ref name=\"preview\">{{cite web|url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/la-fi-ct-movie-projector-america-made-20170927-htmlstory.html|title='It' drives record September box office with Tom Cruise's 'American Made' ready to battle 'Kingsman'|website=[[Los Angeles Times]]|author=Ryan Faughnder|date=September 27, 2017|accessdate=September 27, 2017}}</ref> It ended up debuting to $6.6 million, finishing 5th at the box office; even before factoring in inflation, the number was lower than the $10 million opening of the original film in 1990.<ref name=\"opening\">{{cite web|last1=D'Alessandro|first1=Anthony|title=\u2018Kingsman\u2019 Edges Out \u2018It\u2019 In Fierce Three-Way B.O. Tie; Early AM Figures Have \u2018American Made\u2019 In 3rd \u2013 Monday|url=https://deadline.com/2017/09/tom-cruise-emma-stone-american-made-battle-of-the-sexes-flatliners-weekend-box-office-1202179279/|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|accessdate=October 1, 2017|date=October 2, 2017}}</ref> In its second weekend the film dropped 42%, grossing $3.6 million.<ref>{{cite web|last1=D'Alessandro|first1=Anthony|title=\u2018Blade Runner 2049\u2019 Still Rusted With $36M+ Columbus Day Weekend Opening: Monday Postmortem|url=https://deadline.com/2017/10/blade-runner-2049-ryan-gosling-box-office-bomb-1202184297/|website=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=October 8, 2017|date=October 9, 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Critical response===\n{{Expand section|date=August 2018}}<!-- individual critics needed -->\nOn review aggregation website [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the film has an approval rating of 4% based on 76 reviews and an average rating of 3.53/10. The site's critical consensus reads, \"''Flatliners'' falls flat as a horror movie and fails to improve upon its source material, rendering this reboot dead on arrival.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/flatliners_2017|title=Flatliners (2017)|publisher=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|accessdate=October 3, 2019}}</ref> On [[Metacritic]], which assigns a normalized rating to reviews, the film has a weighted average score of 27 out of 100 based 20 critics, indicating \"generally unfavorable reviews\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://metacritic.com/movie/flatliners-2017|title=Flatliners reviews|publisher=[[Metacritic]]|accessdate=October 6, 2017}}</ref> Audiences polled by [[CinemaScore]] gave the film an average grade of \"B\u2013\" on an A+ to F scale, while [[PostTrak]] reported filmgoers gave it a 66% overall positive score and a 46% \"definite recommend\".<ref name=opening/><ref>{{cite web|title=Is the Flatliners remake any good?|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-41468941|website=BBC News|accessdate=October 6, 2017|date=October 2, 2017}}</ref>\n\nCriticizing the repetitiveness of the scenes and lack of tension, [[Peter Travers]] of ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' called the film \"even more witless and stupefyingly dull than the original.\" He gave it one star.<ref name=RStone>{{cite web |last=Travers |first=Peter |authorlink=Peter Travers |title=Flatliners Review: This Thriller Remake Is a Fright-Free Fiasco |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/movies/movie-reviews/flatliners-review-this-thriller-remake-is-a-fright-free-fiasco-253532/ |website=[[Rolling Stone]] |accessdate=20 March 2020 |date=September 29, 2017}}</ref> Ryan Porter gave it one-and-a-half stars in ''[[Toronto Star|The Star]]'', saying that like the original, it takes a solid premise and fails to develop it in an interesting or exciting way. He said the film's one positive is the unintentional humor which results from the stupidity of several scenes and the earnestness with which the actors approach them.<ref name=Starrev>{{cite web |last=Porter |first=Ryan |title=Flatliners Amounts to Uninspired, Redudant Viewing Experience |url=https://www.thestar.com/entertainment/movies/2017/09/30/flatliners-amounts-to-uninspired-redundant-viewing-experience-review.html |website=[[Toronto Star|The Star]] |accessdate=20 March 2020 |date=September 30, 2017}}</ref> [[Matt Zoller Seitz]] similarly said that \"[the] premise [of the original ''Flatliners''], which could have opened the door to a visionary work of sci-fi horror, settled into a sort of gothic self-help drama groove, with the medical students realizing that the seemingly supernatural goings-on triggered by their experiments in 'flatlining' were manifestations of their past misdeeds. Director Niels Arden Oplev's remake ... sticks to that template, changing key details here and there while embracing a style that stirs every current horror movie visual cliche into a jagged paste.\" He also remarked that the obvious effort given by the entire cast could not overcome the contrived and cliched scares and melodrama.<ref>{{cite web |last=Seitz |first=Matt Zoller |authorlink=Matt Zoller Seitz |title=Flatliners Movie Review |url=https://www.rogerebert.com/reviews/flatliners-2017 |website=[[RogerEbert.com]] |accessdate=20 March 2020 |date=September 29, 2017}}</ref> Both Travers and Porter derided the visual effect of the afterlife scenes as cheap-looking and silly.<ref name=RStone/><ref name=Starrev/>\n\n===Home media===\n''Flatliners'' was released on [[Digital distribution|Digital HD]] on December 12, 2017, and on [[Blu-ray]] and [[DVD]] on December 19, 2017 in Canada, and on December 26, 2017 in the United States.<ref>{{cite web|title=Flatliners synopsis and movie info|url=https://www.tribute.ca/movies/flatliners/70262/|website=Tribute.ca|accessdate=December 27, 2017|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Flatliners DVD Release Date December 26, 2017|url=https://www.dvdsreleasedates.com/movies/8091/flatliners|website=DVDs Release Dates|accessdate=December 27, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* ''[[A Thousand Deaths (London short story)|A Thousand Deaths]]''\n\n==Notes==\n{{Notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://www.sonypictures.com/movies/flatliners}}\n* {{IMDb title|2039338|Flatliners}}\n* {{Amg title|124728|Flatliners}}\n* {{Rotten Tomatoes|flatliners_2017}}\n\n{{Niels Arden Oplev}}\n{{Michael Douglas}}\n\n[[Category:2017 films]]\n[[Category:2017 horror films]]\n[[Category:2010s psychological drama films]]\n[[Category:2010s science fiction drama films]]\n[[Category:2010s science fiction horror films]]\n[[Category:2010s psychological horror films]]\n[[Category:2010s psychological thriller films]]\n[[Category:2010s supernatural horror films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American psychological drama films]]\n[[Category:American psychological horror films]]\n[[Category:American psychological thriller films]]\n[[Category:American science fiction drama films]]\n[[Category:American science fiction horror films]]\n[[Category:American science fiction thriller films]]\n[[Category:American supernatural horror films]]\n[[Category:American supernatural thriller films]]\n[[Category:Columbia Pictures films]]\n[[Category:Cross Creek Pictures films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:Films about death]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Niels Arden Oplev]]\n[[Category:Films set in 2008]]\n[[Category:Films set in 2017]]\n[[Category:Films produced by Laurence Mark]]\n[[Category:Films produced by Michael Douglas]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Toronto]]\n[[Category:Horror film remakes]]\n[[Category:Medical-themed films]]\n[[Category:Near-death experiences in fiction]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox film\n| name = Flatliners\n| image = Flatliners (2017).jpg\n| caption = Theatrical release poster\n| director = [[Niels Arden Oplev]]\n| producer = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Laurence Mark]]<ref name=\"producers\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/flatliners-trailer-remake-ellen-page-diego-luna-nina-dobrev-1202464050/|title=Ellen Page, Diego Luna, Nina Dobrev Experiment With Death in \u2018Flatliners\u2019 Trailer|last=McNary|first=Dave|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=June 13, 2017|accessdate=June 13, 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Michael Douglas]]<ref name=\"producers\"/>\n* [[Peter Safran]]<ref name=\"producers\"/>\n}}\n| screenplay = [[Ben Ripley]]\n| story = Peter Filardi\n| based on = {{based on|